       fhir:comment [ fhir:v "MedicationStatement is a statement at a point in time.  The status is only representative at the point when it was asserted.  The value set for MedicationStatement.status contains codes that assert the status of the use of the medication by the patient (for example, stopped or on hold) as well as codes that assert the status of the medication statement itself (for example, entered in error).\r\rThis element is labeled as a modifier because the status contains codes that mark the resource as not currently valid." ] ;
